  "text": "After specific treatments, cells were fixed in 4% paraformaldehyde or methanol and washed twice with PBS. Immunocytochemistry assays were performed using anti-DOR (1/200) generated in our laboratory [CITATION_1] , anti-TP53INP1 (1/50, Santa Cruz) and anti-p62 (1/1000, BD). Hoechst (1/2000) (Molecular Probes, Oregon USA) was used to label DNA. Cells were mounted in Fluoromount (Electron Microscopy Sciences).",
